                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Dojo's dijits do not respect all of the inline styling of the original elements they apply to, and instead override them with the currently applied dijit theme. At best, this should be brought up with dojo as an issue.\r\n\r\nThe recommended method from dojo is to apply any customisation through your own stylesheets, or inline stylesheet, and from there you should be able to target specific elements by their ID.\r\n\r\nI am closing this as it is an upstream related problem, and not fixable from within ZF itself.",
